<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Busy1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Busy,</orth> adj., 1) employed with earnestness, active; used of persons and things: <bibl n="shak. ven 383" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 383</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 1790" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1790</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 143.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 143, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 1, 15</bibl> (corr. pass.). <bibl n="shak. ado 1.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 2, 3</bibl> <cit><quote>(he is very b. about it).</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 1.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 2, 3</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.5.6" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.4.62" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 4, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 5.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. V, 1, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 5.2.81" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.2.76" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 2, 76</bibl>. H5 <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.0." default="NO" valid="yes">IV Prol. 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.4.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 4, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.339" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 339</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.145" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 145</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.2.81" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 2, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 2, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 3, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.232" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 232</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.1.241" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 1, 241</bibl> <emph>(he's b. in the paper).</emph><lb />2) in a bad sense, == officious, prying, meddling: <cit><quote>on meddling monkey or on b. ape,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.181" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 181</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the b. meddling fiend,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.3.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 3, 21</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou findest to be too b. is some danger,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 4, 33</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>too b. in my fears,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.253" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 253</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>some b. and insinuating rogue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.131" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 131</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>